Key Findings:
dNN outperformed LSTM and process-based models (median NSE: 
dNN=0.78, LSTM=0.76, EXP-HYDRO=0.63, HBV=0.59); 
dNN predicted only 8/29 catchments with misleading runoff increases vs LSTM's 14/29; 
dNN? captured cold-season runoff increase and warm-season recession better than LSTM; 
dNN? inferred snowpack dynamics with avg correlation 0.74 to SWE data; 
dNN explained non-monotonic runoff in glacial catchments (initial increase then decrease)
